'''''Once More 'Round the Sun'''''  is the sixth studio album from American [[Heavy metal music|heavy metal]]  band [[Mastodon (band)|Mastodon]]. The album was released on June 24, 2014, via [[Reprise Records]].<ref name="blabbermouth">{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/mastodon-high-road-audio-visualizer-clip-posted-online/|title=Mastodon: &#x27;Once More &#x27;Round The Sun&#x27; Cover Artwork, Track Listing Revealed - Blabbermouth.net|publisher=blabbermouth.net|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref>  On April 17, 2014, Mastodon released the album's first single, titled "[[High Road (Mastodon song)|High Road]]".<ref name="blabbermouth2">{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/mastodon-new-song-high-road-available-for-streaming/|title=Mastodon: New Song &#x27;High Road&#x27; Available For Streaming - Blabbermouth.net|publisher=blabbermouth.net|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref> On June 16, 2014 the album was made available for streaming on [[iTunes]]. The album sold around 34,000 copies in the United States in its first week of release to land at position No. 6 on The Billboard 200 chart, making it the band's second consecutive top 10 debut after their previous album, ''The Hunter'', peaked at No.10 after opening with 39,000 copies in 2011.<ref>http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/mastodons-once-more-round-the-sun-cracks-u-s-top-10/</ref>

==Background==
In late 2012, Mastodon guitarist [[Brent Hinds]] mentioned in an interview that he had begun writing material for the band's next release.<ref name="mtvhive">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtvhive.com/2012/10/24/mastodon-new-album/|title=Brent Hinds Is Working on &#8220;Radioheadish,&#8221; &#8220;Spooky Sounding&#8221; Songs for Mastodon &#124; MTV Hive|publisher=mtvhive.com|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref>
The band continued writing and demoing their sixth studio album throughout 2013, while touring for their 2011 release ''[[The Hunter (Mastodon album)|The Hunter]]''.<ref name="loudwire">{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/mastodon-brann-dailor-new-album-2013-mayhem-festival-more/|title=Mastodon&#8217;s Brann Dailor Talks New Album Progress, 2013 Mayhem Festival + More|publisher=loudwire.com|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref> The band began recording in late 2013 at Rock Falcon Studios in [[Franklin, Tennessee]], with producer [[Nick Raskulinecz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2014/02/mastodon-new-album-interview/|title=Mastodon Near Completion of 'Wild' Summer LP  &#124; SPIN &#124; Profiles &#124; In The Studio|publisher=spin.com|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref><ref name="pastemagazine">{{cite web|url=http://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2014/04/mastodons-troy-sanders-talks-new-album-once-more-r.html|title=Mastodon&#39;s Troy Sanders Talks New Album Once More &#39;Round the Sun :: Music :: News :: Paste|publisher=pastemagazine.com|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref>

==Musical style==
[[Troy Sanders]] has stated in an interview that the album is a continuation, where the band left off with their previous album (''[[The Hunter (Mastodon album)|The Hunter]]'').<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/upcoming_releases/mastodon_new_material_picks_up_where_the_hunter_left_off.html |title=Mastodon: 'New Material Picks Up Where 'The Hunter' Left Off' &#124; Music News @ |publisher=Ultimate-guitar.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref>

[[Bill Kelliher]] stated also about the album's musical style: "We're always trying to surprise ourselves and write something that's new and fresh. It's definitely got the elements of ''The Hunter'' in there, but also [of] ''[[Remission (Mastodon album)|Remission]]'' and some heavier stuff. There's a lot of different influences, from [[Alice in Chains]] to [[Deftones]]. There's a lot of [[rock music|rock]] going on."<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/upcoming_releases/mastodon_guitarist_on_the_new_record_theres_a_lot_of_rock_going_on.html |title=Mastodon Guitarist on the New Record: 'There's a Lot of Rock Going On' &#124; Music News @ |publisher=Ultimate-guitar.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref>

[[Brann Dailor]] stated following about the album: "It's gonna be massive and insane, lots of epic greatness. There will be lots of huge riffs and new directions. It's real weird, real [[math rock|math-y]], real straightforward. It's up, down and all around."<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/entertainment/mastodon_announce_weird_mathy_stevie_wonder-inspired_album_confirm_nick_raskulinecz_as_producer.html |title=Mastodon Announce 'Weird, Mathy,' Stevie Wonder-Inspired Album, Confirm Nick Raskulinecz as Producer &#124; Music News @ |publisher=Ultimate-guitar.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref>

Kelliher also stated that the album's theme might be "[[death]]". He stated the following: "It always makes for really good story telling. It's kind of the theme that we have a lot in our music. We've had a lot of friends pass away since the last record. I'm not really sure yet. I think we're kind of focusing more about living on this earth and what would happen if this was your last year to live. I think that's sort of maybe a little bit of what we might be kind of touching on."<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/upcoming_releases/mastodon_guitarist_on_new_album_death_is_always_a_good_theme.html |title=Mastodon Guitarist on New Album: 'Death Is Always a Good Theme' &#124; Music News @ |publisher=Ultimate-guitar.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref>

==Artwork==
Oakland-based artist Skinner, who characterizes his work as "psychedelic nightmare paintings," created the album's artwork. Prior to its release, bassist and vocalist Troy Sanders stated: "It's going to be a work of art for sure. It's going to be very eye-opening. Very striking. It's from another dimension, and a lot of our music is geared toward that idea—taking you to another planet on songs. It's out there, and I think it's incredible."<ref>{{cite web|last=Kane |first=Tyler |url=http://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2014/04/mastodons-troy-sanders-talks-new-album-once-more-r.html |title=Mastodon's Troy Sanders Talks New Album Once More 'Round the Sun :: Music :: News :: Paste |publisher=Pastemagazine.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref>

